    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        WINDSHIELD WASHER (ELECTRIC)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>WINDSHIELD WASHER (ELECTRIC)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The windshield washer system (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600683">Figure 83</hotlnk>) consists of an inside cab mounted reservoir with an
                integral electric powered pump motor. The system will deliver washer solvent to the windshield through
                hoses and nozzles in the wiper arms. Reservoir and pump motor are located directly behind the driver's
                seat. All components are available for service.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600683" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600683" filename="../figg16/g1600683.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Windshield Washer Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. NOZZLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WIRE CONTROL SWITCH-TO-MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PUMP MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. RESERVOIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HOSE, PUMP-TO-WIPER NOZZLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
